cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of generative adversarial networks (GANs) by incorporating adversarial dropout. The paper focuses on the application of this approach in the context of multi-adversarial networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.GR (Graphics).
